For this assignment, I interviewed my father who I consider successful in business, he started at 30 years old without a degree or prior knowledge and he could create a great company on his own. I really think that he is a good reference of effort and courage. I asked several open-ended questions about his experiences, past, goals and motivation. Through this interview I learned about being ambitious, time management and overcoming challenges.

When I asked how he would overcome a failure, he said "Failure is an opportunity to learn, the problem is when you keep doing the same mistakes". He emphasizes  improving through experiences, once you make a mistake, analyze, learn and try to do things different next time.

When discussing goals, he described goals an opportunity to put pressure in our journey. He explained when we don't have pressure, we probably would be lazy and less focused, which leads to a lack of results in the process. He shared an experience when he put a high goal, at the beginning he didn't believe in achieving that goal, but through that month he couldn't stop working on that goal, he wanted to reach the goal, he had pressure since he woke up. Thanks to that goal he could increase his productivity that month as he never did.

Finally, we talked about the best advice that he could give to somebody who is starting in this world, he shared "We should always be looking to network with everyone". He explained that networking is so underrated, through networking we can meet people, customers and solutions. 

Overall, this interview taught me that success is built through goals, learning from failure and see every situation as an opportunity. It helped me open my eyes when I face hard situations and taking advantage of every situation. I also learned the importance of asking questions to people who are successfull, we can save ourselves the learning curve of their mistakes, success and tips.